<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910201-0162</DOCNO><DOCID>910201-0162.</DOCID><HL>   Johns Hopkins Gets   $1.5 Billion Navy Job</HL><DATE>02/01/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A5</SO><CO>   TXN GM GMH WX TRW ESY RTN</CO><IN>AEROSPACE (ARO)</IN><GV>DEFENSE DEPARTMENT (DEF)</GV><LP>   WASHINGTON -- Johns Hopkins University was awarded a $1.5billion Navy contract for research and development onstrategic, tactical and electronics systems.                                                                                                       </LP><TEXT>   Texas Instruments Inc. received a $272.9 million Navycontract for HARM missiles.                                                                                                          Hughes Aircraft Co., a unit of General Motors Corp., gotcontracts totaling $146.5 million for Navy torpedos and Armythermal-imaging systems.                                                                                                          Westinghouse Electric Corp. was issued a $125.5 millionNavy contract for torpedos.                                                                                                          TRW Defense Systems Group, a unit of TRW Inc., got a $29million Army contract for software research and development.                                                                                                          Serv-Air Inc. was awarded a $28 million Army contract forcommunications support.                                                                                                          E-Systems Inc. received a $20.6 million Air Force contractfor aircraft modification.                                                                                                          Raytheon Co. got a $12.8 million Army contract for Patriotmissiles and airport equipment.</TEXT></DOC>